50|$|Since the Class 19B {{was heavy}} on coal, a {{ground-level}} concrete coal bin was built at Graaff-Reinet especially to replenish these locomotives on through runs while {{standing in the}} platform road. There was no standpipe alongside the platform road, however, so even though coal was taken here, <b>through-working</b> engines took water at Charlwood and Pretoriuskloof.|$|E

